# FTP Deployment Configuration for InfinityFree
# Copy this file to .env and fill in your actual values

# InfinityFree FTP Server Details
# Get these from your InfinityFree control panel -> FTP Accounts
FTP_HOST=ftpupload.net
FTP_PORT=21
FTP_USER=your-ftp-username
FTP_PASSWORD=your-ftp-password
FTP_SECURE=false
FTP_REMOTE_DIR=/htdocs

# Deployment Options
# NODE_ENV=production

# Optional: Override default settings
# FTP_TIMEOUT=30000
# FTP_MAX_RETRIES=2

# Instructions:
# 1. Copy this file to .env: cp .env.example .env
# 2. Login to your InfinityFree control panel
# 3. Go to "FTP Accounts" section
# 4. Find your main FTP account details
# 5. Replace the placeholder values above with your actual FTP credentials
# 6. Never commit the .env file to git (it's already in .gitignore)

# GitHub Secrets Setup:
# For GitHub Actions deployment, add these as secrets in your repository:
# Repository Settings > Secrets and variables > Actions > New repository secret
#
# Required secrets:
# - FTP_HOST
# - FTP_USER
# - FTP_PASSWORD
# - FTP_REMOTE_DIR (usually /htdocs for InfinityFree)
#
# Optional secrets:
# - FTP_PORT (defaults to 21)
# - FTP_SECURE (defaults to false)